# Intent Card Rules

Intent cards define the canonical support knowledge.
They are NOT free-form documents.

Each intent card MUST include:

- intent_id (string, unique)
- title (short human-readable)
- description (1–2 sentences)
- symptoms (list of observable user symptoms)
- hidden_root_causes (list, NEVER shown to support agent)
- required_questions (list of questions agent should ask)
- resolution_paths (list of valid resolution strategies)
- forbidden_actions (list of incorrect or risky actions)
- escalation_rules (conditions when escalation is allowed)
- common_agent_mistakes (allowed mistake types for this intent)

Rules:

- Support agent sees ONLY:
  - symptoms
  - required_questions
  - resolution_paths
  - forbidden_actions
  - escalation_rules

- Customer simulator sees:
  - hidden_root_causes
  - symptoms
  - mapping of answers → questions

- Judge sees the FULL intent card.

Intent cards must NOT:
- Encode dialogue flow
- Contain prompt text
- Include emotional or stylistic instructions
- Reference specific LLM behavior

If an intent card is missing required fields,
AI assistants must STOP and ask to fix the schema.